After last night's snow.
The group, centre middle distance, are doing keep fit and calesthenics including lying on their backs in the snow...
Pentland Hills near Edinburgh, Scotland Panorama
Morning snow; it fell a couple of nights ago but it was too wet to lie on the streets. Some gardens, etc. got a couple of inches - more on the outskirts.

title._content: Scott Memorial in Snow, Edinburgh, January 2011

description._content: Looking south, from beside the tennis courts

09.01.10 - Beautiful memorial which caught my eye on my way home from a bike ride.  I know that's two graveyards in two days now, so I hope it won't be a recurring theme!  The light was just catching this perfectly.
First attempt (well, one of many, but first set up really!) at self portrait.  Taken on Poet's Glen, Pentland Hills

Looking almost due south down Causewayside.
I used to go to that little church on the horizon!
someone has hung "wreaths" of seed and suet for the birds in the trees at the side of the canal
